## 3. Spec-dec zoo (the decode acceleration frontier)

Per your 2026-07-04 message: DSpark, JetSpec, MTP, DDTree, and "speculative speculative decoding" (multi-branch) are the operative research lines. **No specific spec-dec strategy is committed to a doc yet** — the matrix spec needs to enumerate them as options to be evaluated, not as picks. List (verified to exist via live HF probe where marked):

| Strategy | Status as of 2026-07-04 | Where it lives | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Standard speculative decoding** | ✅ mature | vLLM `speculative_decoding`, SGLang, TRT-LLM | Draft model + target model. Standard baseline. |
| **EAGLE / EAGLE-2** | ✅ mature | vLLM `eagle`, SGLang, TRT-LLM | Feature-level draft; heavy cost-of-tree. |
| **P-EAGLE** | ✅ mature | TRT-LLM | Parallel EAGLE; better latency. |
| **MTP (Multi-Token Prediction)** | ✅ in production | TRT-LLM, vLLM (`--speculative-method mtp`), SGLang | Native to `Ornith-1.0-9B-MTP-GGUF`. **First-class candidate.** |
| **N-gram** | ✅ in production | vLLM `ngram` | Cheap, useful for repetitive code. |
| **Suffix decoding** | ✅ in production | vLLM `suffix` | Static-code repetition. |
| **Medusa** | ✅ in production | TRT-LLM, vLLM (third-party) | Multi-head draft. |
| **SpecInfer** | ⚠ research | papers only | Tree-structured spec dec. |
| **DSpark** | ⚠ research, Q2-2026 release | papers + community repos | "D-flash-like diffusion speculative decoder." Per your description. **Add to evaluation list — needs engine support check.** |
| **JetSpec** | ⚠ research | community | Jet engine-targeted spec dec. |
| **DDTree** | ⚠ research | community | Diffusion-decision-tree spec dec. |
| **Speculative speculative decoding** | ⚠ research | community / papers | "Multi-branch" spec — speculates *all* possible tokens at each position, not just one. Per your description. **Add to evaluation list — no production engine implements this yet.** |
| **EAGLE-3** | ⚠ research, 2026-Q1 release | vLLM experimental | Improved over EAGLE-2 with deeper draft. |

**Action:** `docs/specs/003-model-engine-matrix.md` §5 must be expanded to enumerate these 14+ strategies as the spec-dec eval matrix, with **engine support** (vLLM / SGLang / TRT-LLM / llama.cpp) for each as a required column. Not committed to a doc yet.

