## 4. Recency cutoff control rule (added to ADR 0004 rule #6)

Per your 2026-07-04 message: **"heavily heavily enforced to look at models released no earlier than March 2026 without deep justification."**

**Rule #6 (new):**

- Any HF repo with `last_modified < 2026-03-01 UTC` is `recency_dlq` (deferred low-quality) by default.
- A pre-March model stays in the matrix only with a `deep-justification` block in `v2_shortlist.md` §X named explicitly.
- `v2_shortlist.md` is regenerated weekly; the date stamp is on every entry.
- Pre-March OR models where the **HF repo is current** (e.g. `lfm-2-24b-a2b` OR 2026-02-25 / HF 2026-03-30) are NOT `recency_dlq` — the canonical repo is the source of truth.
- Pre-March OR models where the **HF repo is also pre-March AND not updated** (e.g. `granite-4.0-h-micro`) ARE `recency_dlq` and require explicit keep/drop.

